NAME
    date - print or set the system date and time

SYNOPSIS
    date [-f FORMAT]
    date [[YYYY-MM-DD] hh:mm:ss]

DESCRIPTION
    Display the current time in the given FORMAT, or set the system date. When disaplying the date,
    the following formats can be specified:

    -f 0
        Complete: results in something like: 2023-06-07 16:58:16 - epoch 1686149896

    -f 1
        Timestamp: results in something like: 2023-06-07 16:58:16

    -f 2
        Date: results in something like: 2023-06-07

    -f 3
        Time: results in something like: 16:58:16

EXAMPLES
    date
        Displays the current date or time

